---
const title = "Getting Started";
import Layout from "../../../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout title={title}>
  <h2>Permission</h2>
  <p>
    Please fill out the <a href="/assets/permission-student-work.pdf"
      >Permission to use Student Work PDF and upload the completed form to this <a
        href="https://drive.google.com/drive/folders/1aQlhBAs7xxmVOeIoasI4oItJAQEOI34D?usp=drive_link"
        >Google Drive</a
      > folder.</a
    >.
  </p>
  <h2>Software</h2>
  <p>
    For design, we will use Figma and FigJam.
    <a href="https://www.figma.com/education/"
      >Verify for an education license</a
    >.
  </p>
  <p>
    For our class, we will use
    <a href="https://code.visualstudio.com/"
      >Microsoft Visual Studio Code (VS Code)</a
    >
    as our text editor.
  </p>
  <p>
    You'll also need the
    <a
      href="https://marketplace.visualstudio.com/items?itemName=ritwickdey.LiveServer"
      >Live Server</a
    >
    extension, which automatically refreshes the browser whenever we save our files
    in VS Code.
  </p>
  <p>
    Lastly, you'll want to use
    <a
      href="https://marketplace.visualstudio.com/items?itemName=esbenp.prettier-vscode"
      >Prettier</a
    >
    and configure it to
    <a
      href="https://www.freecodecamp.org/news/how-to-use-prettier-in-visual-studio-code/"
      >format your files upon save</a
    >.
  </p>
  <hr />
  <h2>Browser Inspectors</h2>
  <p>
    Familiarize yourself with browser inspectors, as these tools will prove
    essential in writing and troubleshooting your code.
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>
      <a href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Tools/Page_Inspector"
        >Firefox Page Inspector</a
      >
    </li>
    <li>
      <a href="https://developer.chrome.com/devtools">Chrome Dev Tools</a>
    </li>
    <li>
      <a href="https://developer.apple.com/safari/tools/"
        >Safari Developer Tools</a
      >
    </li>
  </ul>
  <hr />
  <h2>Github</h2>
  <p>
    Lastly, you'll want to create a free personal
    <a href="https://github.com/">GitHub</a> account. You'll probably want to download
    <a href="https://desktop.github.com/">GitHub Desktop</a> as you'll use it to
    set up your <a href="https://pages.github.com/">GitHub pages</a>.
  </p>
</Layout>
